                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/671.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-03T23:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 3, 1912—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A message from the President to Congress to-day asking for authority to suspend
                    constitutional guaranties, in all or part of the Republic as circumstances may
                    demand. Congress to consider matter to-morrow in special session.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
